      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Ed Schröder</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"http://www.rebel.nl/whoiswho.htm\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/97/SchroderChampion_1992.jpg/300px-SchroderChampion_1992.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"411\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/9/97/SchroderChampion_1992.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:SchroderChampion_1992.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ed Schröder, <a href=\"/WCCC_1992\" title=\"WCCC 1992\">WCCC Madrid 1992</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Ed Schröder</b>, (Ed Schroder)<br />\na Dutch computer chess programmer and founder of <b>Schröder BV</b> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, a chess software developing company. Ed is author of various chess programs for PCs as well for <a href=\"/Dedicated_Chess_Computers\" title=\"Dedicated Chess Computers\">dedicated chess computers</a>. His most famous chess programs were the commercial programs <a href=\"/Rebel\" title=\"Rebel\">Rebel</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, and based on Rebel the <a href=\"/WMCCC_1991\" title=\"WMCCC 1991\">WMCCC 1991</a> Micro Champion <a href=\"/Gideon\" title=\"Gideon\">Gideon</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>, the World Computer Chess Champion from the <a href=\"/WCCC_1992\" title=\"WCCC 1992\">WCCC 1992</a>, <a href=\"/ChessMachine\" title=\"ChessMachine\">ChessMachine</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>, and the free program <a href=\"/ProDeo\" title=\"ProDeo\">ProDeo</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>. Ed contributed a lot to computer chess, since he made almost all his knowledge about chess programming <a href=\"/Recommended_Reading\" title=\"Recommended Reading\">public</a>, when he retired from competition in 2003 <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>. In 2002 <a href=\"/Lokasoft\" title=\"Lokasoft\">Lokasoft</a> took over the activities of <b>Schröder BV</b> <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#2011_Rybka_Controversy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2011 Rybka Controversy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Programs_and_Computers\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Programs and Computers</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#1993_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1993 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#1995_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1995 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#2005_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2005 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#2015_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-13\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2011_Rybka_Controversy\">2011 Rybka Controversy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ed_Schroder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: 2011 Rybka Controversy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>In 2011, Ed Schröder first signed the <a href=\"/Open_letter_to_the_ICGA_about_the_Rybka-Fruit_issue\" title=\"Open letter to the ICGA about the Rybka-Fruit issue\">open letter</a> directed to the <a href=\"/ICGA\" title=\"ICGA\">ICGA</a>, to support the claim <a href=\"/Rybka\" title=\"Rybka\">Rybka 1.0 beta</a> and subsequent versions were allegedly derivatives from <a href=\"/Fabien_Letouzey\" title=\"Fabien Letouzey\">Fabien Letouzey’s</a> program <a href=\"/Fruit\" title=\"Fruit\">Fruit 2.1</a>, but soon after the <a href=\"/Rybka_Controversy#RybkaDecision\" title=\"Rybka Controversy\">ICGA decision</a>, reconsidered <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>, apologized to <a href=\"/Vasik_Rajlich\" title=\"Vasik Rajlich\">Vasik Rajlich</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> and criticized the <a href=\"/ICGA_Investigations\" title=\"ICGA Investigations\">investigation process</a> and the represented evidence. In November 2011, Ed Schröder announced his new web-sites <sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> that give an alternative view of the historic ICGA - RYBKA event that led to the ban of Rybka.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Programs_and_Computers\">Programs and Computers</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ed_Schroder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Programs and Computers\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/ChessMachine\" title=\"ChessMachine\">ChessMachine</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Gideon\" title=\"Gideon\">Gideon</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mephisto_MM_IV\" title=\"Mephisto MM IV\">Mephisto MM IV</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mephisto_MM_V\" title=\"Mephisto MM V\">Mephisto MM V</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mephisto_Polgar\" title=\"Mephisto Polgar\">Mephisto Polgar</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mephisto_Rebell\" title=\"Mephisto Rebell\">Mephisto Rebell</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mephisto_RISC\" title=\"Mephisto RISC\">Mephisto RISC</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/ProDeo\" title=\"ProDeo\">ProDeo</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Rebel\" title=\"Rebel\">Rebel</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ed_Schroder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Jeroen_Noomen\" title=\"Jeroen Noomen\">Jeroen Noomen</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i>Anand versus Rebel 10 exp.</i> <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#21_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 21, No. 3</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>How Rebel Plays Chess</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://silo.tips/download/how-rebel-plays-chess-1\">pdf</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ed_Schroder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1993_...\">1993 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ed_Schroder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 1993 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rec.games.chess/B0kdQBurQII/znCLMkBHjF4J\">Interview with world champ chess programmer (long)</a> by Kees de Graaf, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgc</a>, February 05, 1993</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1995_...\">1995 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ed_Schroder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 1995 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rec.games.chess/drr9JHQKHrA/hkz9kAAqvWIJ\">REBEL 7 announcement</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgc</a>, July 27, 1995</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rec.games.chess.computer/baCTtjjm0cs/m22XLVBDfGUJ\">Open letter to ChessBase</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, January 09, 1997</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=10361\">CCC-I test set</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 04, 1997&#160;» <a href=\"/Test-Positions\" title=\"Test-Positions\">Test-Positions</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=10362\">CCC-II test set</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 04, 1997</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=10391\">CCC-III (positional test)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 06, 1997</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=14226\">Hash tables and data-cache, some programmer stuff...</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 17, 1998&#160;» <a href=\"/Hash_Table\" title=\"Hash Table\">Hash Table</a>, <a href=\"/Transposition_Table\" title=\"Transposition Table\">Transposition Table</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=23055\">My views on the Match</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 27, 1998</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/msg/rec.games.chess.computer/T0KphUfUTi8/R0ibWxvqMu0J\">Ed's real life</a> by <a href=\"/Jean-Christophe_Weill\" title=\"Jean-Christophe Weill\">Jean-Christophe Weill</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">rgcc</a>, August 15, 1998</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=29817\">How to create a set of random integers for hashing?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 18, 1998&#160;» <a href=\"/Zobrist_Hashing\" title=\"Zobrist Hashing\">Zobrist Hashing</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=42019\">AUTO232 and memory protection</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 03, 1999&#160;» <a href=\"/Auto232\" title=\"Auto232\">Auto232</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=72537\">PB-ON vs PB-OFF (results experiment-1)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 10, 1999&#160;» <a href=\"/Pondering\" title=\"Pondering\">Pondering</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=73408\">PB-ON vs PB-OFF (final results)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 15, 1999</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ed_Schroder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=129504\">Faster, deeper and more of such...</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 14, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Depth#DiminishingReturns\" title=\"Depth\">Diminishing Returns</a>, <a href=\"/Search_Statistics\" title=\"Search Statistics\">Search Statistics</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=143151\">Marcus Kastner versus Millennium (again)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 06, 2000&#160;» <a href=\"/Marcus_K%C3%A4stner\" title=\"Marcus Kästner\">Marcus Kästner</a>, <a href=\"/Millennium_2000_GmbH\" title=\"Millennium 2000 GmbH\">Millennium 2000 GmbH</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=182383\">Maastricht</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 03, 2001&#160;» <a href=\"/WMCCC_2001\" title=\"WMCCC 2001\">WMCCC 2001</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=240056\">The law of diminishing returns</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 12, 2002&#160;» <a href=\"/Depth#DiminishingReturns\" title=\"Depth\">Diminishing Returns</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=258559\">Eric Schiller about the Cadaques Qualifier</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 11, 2002&#160;» <a href=\"/Eric_Schiller\" title=\"Eric Schiller\">Eric Schiller</a>, <a href=\"/Kramnik_versus_Deep_Fritz_2002\" title=\"Kramnik versus Deep Fritz 2002\">Kramnik versus Deep Fritz 2002</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=268861\">In memorandum - Jan Louwman</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 04, 2002&#160;» <a href=\"/Jan_Louwman\" title=\"Jan Louwman\">Jan Louwman</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=285555\">Programmer challenge</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 20, 2003&#160;» <a href=\"/X86\" title=\"X86\">x86</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=400589\">Is there a way?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 13, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/Engine_Testing\" title=\"Engine Testing\">Engine Testing</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2005_...\">2005 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ed_Schroder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: 2005 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=443750\">Where are all the congrats to Anthony Cozzie&#160;???</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 21, 2005&#160;» <a href=\"/WCCC_2005\" title=\"WCCC 2005\">WCCC 2005</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=445557\">Expert Assembler Question</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schröder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 26, 2005&#160;» <a href=\"/X86\" title=\"X86\">x86</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=23341\">To campaign or not</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ed Schroder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, Augus